stylometry: Risksimtable allows you to put in information about a problem and have several different simulations running at the same time and it will give you answers based on the informaiton you put into the model.  YOu can have several of these going so you are able to see the differences in the simulations that you performed.  Risk simtable would be used in a simulation model if you wanted to determine how much inventory needs to be ordered and based on demand how much you would have in excess and accumulate holding costs.  You could put three or more different quantities of inventory you order and allow demand to be constant and see the different numbers of leftover inventory.  In some cases the demand can fluctuate so you might want to use the simulation model to change the demand and see what the leftover inventory is.  IT will give you different answers based on the different or same scenarios and as a company you compare the answers and see what level of risk or what answer to the problem you are going to take.
